        "timestamp": "2020-06-12 13:44:58.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nPatchset #3 adds \"findPlugins.sh\".  This code isn't used (at least not yet).  It uses the Nexus API to query the repo to see what plugins are available.  It's useful just to do a quick check of what's in the repo.  Possibly we could move to using this to get the plugins that we store into the CM image, instead of having a hard-coded list.   Putting the code here because I did not want to lose the work.",
        "patchset_number": 4
      },
